crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a trojan downloader and backdoor. It performs process hollowing by creating a suspended process named "abxplore.exe" (a typo-squat of iexplore.exe), unmapping its memory, and injecting its own code. The malware conducts reconnaissance by executing `systeminfo` and `dir` commands on system folders, redirecting the output to a file. It then exfiltrates this data to a hardcoded C2 server and downloads a subsequent payload for execution. Key IOCs include the domain `ink.inkboom.co.kr` and the C2 paths `/host/img/jpg/post.php` (upload) and `/host/img/jpg/download.php` (download).
